{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fa0f7527-f13b-40a3-9bc3-dd8d2c69d4e4","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — no longer supported (EOL)\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — no longer supported (EOL)\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported (.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2)\n\nYou'll need to update your target frameworks to currently supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`, or later) before upgrading.\n\n**Other MSTest v3 changes to be aware of:**\n1. **Package consolidation** — you can replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references with a single `MSTest` meta-package.\n2. **Breaking API changes** — some APIs were removed or renamed; review your test code for deprecated usage.\n3. **`Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** — ensure you're on a compatible version (17.6+).\n\n**Bottom line:** Your biggest blocker is the two unsupported TFMs (`net5.0`, `netcoreapp3.1`). Migrate those first, then upgrade MSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc2c842e-b33f-4f49-aae5-464bffea294d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me check what the compatibility requirements are for MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest.TestFramework 3.x) dropped support for:\n- .NET Framework versions below 4.6.2 — wait, actually `net462` is .NET Framework 4.6.2, which might still be supported\n- .NET Core 3.1 — this was dropped\n- .NET 5.0 — this was dropped\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. \n\nMSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, but dropped support for .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0, requiring .NET 6.0 or later for the newer frameworks. So the user would run into compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`, while `net462` should remain compatible.","outputTokens":773,"requestId":"4C26:22361C:295769:307BE6:6A01423A"},"id":"8eb50e2d-c8d7-49